{"word":"H4347 - מַכָּה - makkâh - mak-kaw' - Beaten","slug":"H4347","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">מַכָּה</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>makkâh"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>mak-kaw'"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Beaten"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x05DE;&#x05DB;&#x05BC;&#x05D4;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&#x05DE;&#x05DB;&#x05BC;&#x05D4; - makka&#x0302;h  makkeh</b> - <i>mak-kaw', mak-keh'</i><p/>(Plural only) from <a href=\"#/H5221\">H5221</a>; a <i>blow</i> (in <a href='B:140 2:10'>2Ch 2:10</a>, of the flail); by implication a <i>wound</i>; figuratively <i>carnage</i>, also <i>pestilence: - </i>beaten, blow, plague, slaughter, smote, X sore, stripe, stroke, wound ([-ed])."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/H3559\">H3559</a>, <a href=\"#/H5221\">H5221</a>, <a href=\"#/H5222\">H5222</a>, <a href=\"#/H5223\">H5223</a>, <a href=\"#/H5224\">H5224</a>, <a href=\"#/H6549\">H6549</a>"}]}